snippet: The police on Wednesday removed a piece of plane wreckage discovered in Lower Manhattan, while an examination of the area yielded no remains.
abstract: New York City officials say that no human remains were found in soil behind building in Lower Manhattan where surveyors discovered wreckage believed to be from one of planes that crashed into World Trade Center; surprising discovery so long after September 11 attacks led to exhaustive search for human remains.
lead_paragraph: The police on Wednesday removed a piece of plane wreckage discovered in Lower Manhattan, while an examination of the area yielded no remains.
